{"key":"post-8619129","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>8619129</id>\n<content>I think what prisoner was referring to was letting it fruit right from the pvc log.&amp;nbsp; I've done those with 3/8&quot; holes drilled four inches apart down the length of the pipe.&amp;nbsp; Tape over the holes with micropore tape during colonization, and then remove the tape for fruiting.&amp;nbsp; If you use that method, alternate spawn and straw while packing, and pack it with most of your weight.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Straw has to be cut into 1&quot; to 4&quot; pieces to make it easier for the mycelium to penetrate into the center.&amp;nbsp; We can pack it tight because there's so much air in straw, as you can see from the microscope picture below of a cross section of a piece of wheat straw.&lt;br /&gt;RR&lt;br /&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://files.shroomery.org/files/07-006/108452877-SEM_of_Straw.jpg&quot; class=&quot;highslide&quot; onclick=&quot;return hs.expand(this,{slideshowGroup:'hsg1'})&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;&lt;img style=&quot;max-width:192px;height:auto;&quot; src=&quot;/forums/thumbs/07-006/108452877-thumb_SEM_of_Straw.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>8619805</next>\n<prev>8618512</prev>\n<first>8609313</first>\n<last>8623189</last>\n<when>1215741286</when>\n<utime>07/11/08 04:54 AM</utime>\n</post>"}